The paper deals with lower bounds for data structures in the context of Bregman divergences, which are commonly used in clustering and nearest neighbor search. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The focus on lower bounds and algorithmic analysis suggests that cs.DS and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CG and cs.LG. The mention of hypercontractivity and isoperimetric inequalities suggests a possible connection to cs.DM.
